Secure CI/CD Pipeline with Role-Based Access & Environment Promotion Strategy

This project demonstrates a secure CI/CD pipeline implementation using Jenkins, Terraform, and AWS EC2 with Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) and an environment promotion strategy to ensure controlled and secure application deployments.

The pipeline automates the build, infrastructure provisioning, and deployment process, while maintaining strict access control and environment separation.

📌 Project Overview 
Modern DevOps practices require secure and automated pipelines.

This project implements a CI/CD pipeline that includes:

Automated build process
Infrastructure provisioning using Terraform

Jenkins-based CI/CD pipeline
Webhook integration for automated triggers

Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
Environment promotion strategy for controlled deployments

🏗 Architecture
Developer pushes code → GitHub triggers Webhook → Jenkins Pipeline runs → Terraform provisions infrastructure → Application deployed on AWS EC2
Copy code

Developer → GitHub → Webhook → Jenkins Pipeline → Terraform → AWS EC2
