⚙️ Pipeline Workflow

1️⃣ Build Stage
Jenkins automatically triggers the pipeline via GitHub Webhook.
The build process verifies the application and dependencies.

![](Image/build.png)


2️⃣ Infrastructure Provisioning
Infrastructure is created using Terraform.
Command used:
Bash
Copy code
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
![](./image/g)

3️⃣ Deployment Stage
Application deployed on AWS EC2 server.
Jenkins manages deployment securely.
![](./image/ec2server.png)

4️⃣ Webhook Integration
GitHub webhook triggers Jenkins automatically whenever code is pushed to the repository.
![](./image/webhook.png)

🔐 Security Implementation
The pipeline includes several security practices:
Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) in Jenkins
Controlled deployment permissions
Secure infrastructure provisioning with Terraform
Environment promotion strategy to prevent unauthorized deployments
🔁 Environment Promotion Strategy
Deployment follows a controlled promotion model:
Copy code

Development → Staging → Production
Only authorized roles can promote builds between environments.

